<br>
Of course I could go into the standard arguments that lazy ass windows programmers can't code their way out of a paper bag, and just don't know how to write decent code for a mac.. but that would quickly get this moved to the flameboard.<br>
<br>
Or I could say that there are still some things that, despite the millions of developers working on other platforms, Mac simply kicks everyone's ass at (security, fonts come to mind).. but that will just start an argument that will get this moved to the flameboard.<br>
<br>
Cogs, you page doesn't display properly because you're using Dreamweaver to code HTML, and flash for your entire content.  <br>
<br>
I work at an advertising company, where we have no choice but to support everyone (8 or 9 browsers last time I checked), and deliver decent content.  It's not pretty, and it's a pain in the ass, but we do make it cross browser, cross platform.<br>
<br>
For an ad company it's pretty obvious why you need to reach everyone, but there is also a very real reason for individuals to do so as well... to avoid a monopoly (no pun intended).<br>
<br>
Give up on Macs.. fuck netscape.  Opera?  Screw the fat lady.  IE 5.5 on a PC IS a great browser, and it's really easy for people who use dreamweaver to make pretty code, especially if you're just slapping in a flash movie.<br>
<br>
What if people don't have Flash?  Oh sure, you can go to macromedia and read their little independent survey on the penetration rate of their plug-ins -- but it's all bullshit.  They claim Flash is installed in more browsers than javascript and java.  Of course that's an impossibility since the plug-in architecture only came in with version 3 of netscape, and java and javascript have been around longer than that.<br>
<br>
Oh, but that's okay, because Flash can save a java version (albeit limited) of a movie.  Doh, MS just announced they're not supporting Java anymore client side in IE.  Hmm, wonder if they'll ever do that with flash (anyone remember liquid motion)?<br>
<br>
You know what, Mac's rock.  So do PCs.  Flash kicks ass, as does DHTML, netscape, Opera, IE, director, java, ECMA, quicktime, DIVX and AVI.  Don't limit your choices and you won't find yourself in a dead end.<br>
<br>
Get back on your Mac and learn how to make the movies sync better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
